==English==
===Etymology===
Coined after the Montague-Capulet feud in Shakespeare's ''Romeo & Juliet''.  The husband's party is known as the Montague party, while the wife's party is called the Capulet party.

===Noun phrase===
'''[[Romeo]] and [[Juliet]] [[couple]]'''

#A couple who married without parental consent.
#A couple consisting of a member of each two opposing families, parties, or countries. (Based on the Montague-Capulet feud in Shakespeare's ''Romeo & Juliet'')